I think people use DI just because Java constructor syntax is so incredibly verbose:<p><pre><code>    public class MyClass {
      @Inject private String foo;
    }
</code></pre>
versus<p><pre><code>    public class MyClass {
      private String foo;

      @Inject public MyClass(String foo) {
        this.foo = foo;
      }
    }</code></pre>
